‚òï Java 8 (2014) ‚Äì The Game Changer

This is where modern Java really started.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Lambda Expressions

Functional-style programming.

// Before Java 8
Runnable r = new Runnable() {
    public void run() {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
};


Runnable r = () -> System.out.println("Hello");


üëâ Used heavily in Streams, collections, and Spring.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Functional Interfaces

Interface with one abstract method.

@FunctionalInterface
interface MyFunc {
    void sayHello();
}


Built-in ones:

Predicate<T>

Function<T, R>

Consumer<T>

Supplier<T>

3Ô∏è‚É£ Streams API üî•

Process collections in functional style.

List<String> names = Arrays.asList("Ram", "Shyam", "Aman");

names.stream()
     .filter(name -> name.startsWith("A"))
     .forEach(System.out::println);


üí° Used heavily in backend filtering logic.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Default & Static Methods in Interface
interface Test {
    default void show() {
        System.out.println("Default method");
    }
}

5Ô∏è‚É£ Optional Class

Avoids NullPointerException.

Optional<String> name = Optional.ofNullable(getName());
name.ifPresent(System.out::println);

6Ô∏è‚É£ New Date/Time API (java.time)
LocalDate date = LocalDate.now();
LocalDateTime time = LocalDateTime.now();


Much better than Date and Calendar.

‚òï Java 9 (2017)
1Ô∏è‚É£ Module System (Project Jigsaw)
module my.module {
    requires java.sql;
}


Rare in Spring projects but good to know.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Factory Methods for Collections
List<String> list = List.of("A", "B", "C");


Immutable collections.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Stream Improvements
Stream.of(1,2,3,4)
      .takeWhile(n -> n < 3)
      .forEach(System.out::println);

‚òï Java 10
üîπ var Keyword (Local Variable Type Inference)
var name = "Aditya";


‚ö†Ô∏è Only for local variables.

‚òï Java 11 (LTS)

Very important for enterprise.

1Ô∏è‚É£ String Enhancements
"  hello  ".strip();
"".isBlank();
"Hi".repeat(3);

2Ô∏è‚É£ HttpClient API
HttpClient client = HttpClient.newHttpClient();


Modern replacement for HttpURLConnection.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Files read/write methods
String content = Files.readString(Path.of("file.txt"));

‚òï Java 12‚Äì13

Mostly preview features.

Switch Expression (finalized in Java 14)
int result = switch(day) {
    case "MON" -> 1;
    case "TUE" -> 2;
    default -> 0;
};


No need for break statements.

‚òï Java 14
üîπ Records (Preview ‚Üí final in 16)

Immutable data classes.

‚òï Java 15
üîπ Text Blocks
String json = """
{
  "name": "Aditya"
}
""";


Perfect for SQL/JSON in backend.

‚òï Java 16
üî• Records (Final)
public record User(String name, int age) {}


Auto-generates:

constructor

getters

equals()

hashCode()

toString()

üî• Very popular in modern Spring Boot.

‚òï Java 17 (LTS)

Major enterprise version.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Sealed Classes

Restrict inheritance.

public sealed class Shape
    permits Circle, Rectangle {}

final class Circle extends Shape {}


Used in domain modeling.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Pattern Matching for instanceof
if (obj instanceof String s) {
    System.out.println(s.length());
}


Cleaner code.

‚òï Java 18‚Äì19

Mostly improvements + preview.

üîπ Virtual Threads (Preview in 19)

Huge for scalability.

‚òï Java 20

Preview improvements for pattern matching.

‚òï Java 21 (LTS ‚Äì Latest Major)

Very important right now.

1Ô∏è‚É£ Virtual Threads (Final) üöÄ

Lightweight threads.

Thread.startVirtualThread(() -> {
    System.out.println("Running");
});


üî• Game changer for high-concurrency systems.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Pattern Matching for Switch (Final)
switch(obj) {
    case String s -> System.out.println("String: " + s);
    case Integer i -> System.out.println("Integer: " + i);
    default -> {}
}

3Ô∏è‚É£ Record Patterns
if (obj instanceof User(String name, int age)) {
    System.out.println(name);
}

üî• Interview Tip for You (Important)

If interviewer asks:

‚ÄúWhat Java features do you use in your project?‚Äù

You can say:

Java 8 Streams & Lambda

Optional

java.time API

var (Java 10)

Switch expressions

Records (DTO modeling)

Pattern matching

Virtual threads (if using Java 21)





‚òï Java 8 (MOST IMPORTANT ‚Äì GAME CHANGER) üî•üî•üî•
1Ô∏è‚É£ Lambda Expressions üî•

Write concise functional-style code.

list.forEach(e -> System.out.println(e));

2Ô∏è‚É£ Functional Interfaces üî•

Interface with only one abstract method.

@FunctionalInterface
interface MyFunc {
    void run();
}


Examples:

Runnable

Callable

Comparator

Predicate, Function, Consumer, Supplier

3Ô∏è‚É£ Stream API üî•üî•

Process collections in a declarative way.

list.stream()
    .filter(x -> x > 10)
    .map(x -> x * 2)
    .forEach(System.out::println);

4Ô∏è‚É£ Default Methods in Interfaces üî•

Add method implementations without breaking existing classes.

interface A {
    default void show() {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

5Ô∏è‚É£ Optional Class üî•

Avoid NullPointerException.

Optional<String> name = Optional.ofNullable(str);
name.ifPresent(System.out::println);

6Ô∏è‚É£ Method References

Cleaner lambda expressions.

list.forEach(System.out::println);

7Ô∏è‚É£ New Date & Time API üî•

Thread-safe and immutable.

LocalDate.now();
LocalDateTime.now();

8Ô∏è‚É£ Nashorn JavaScript Engine

Run JavaScript inside Java (later deprecated).

9Ô∏è‚É£ Parallel Streams

Multi-core processing.

list.parallelStream().forEach(...);

üî• Java 8 Interview One-Liner

Java 8 introduced functional programming via lambdas, streams, and default methods.

‚òï Java 17 (LTS ‚Äì ENTERPRISE FAVORITE) üî•üî•
1Ô∏è‚É£ Sealed Classes üî•

Restrict which classes can extend a class.

sealed class Shape permits Circle, Square {}

2Ô∏è‚É£ Records üî•üî•

Immutable data carrier class (DTO replacement).

record Employee(int id, String name) {}


Auto-generates:

constructor

getters

equals(), hashCode(), toString()

3Ô∏è‚É£ Pattern Matching for instanceof üî•

No explicit casting.

if (obj instanceof String s) {
    System.out.println(s.length());
}

4Ô∏è‚É£ Switch Expressions üî•üî•

More powerful switch.

int result = switch(day) {
    case 1, 2 -> 10;
    case 3 -> 20;
    default -> 0;
};

5Ô∏è‚É£ Text Blocks üî•

Multi-line strings.

String sql = """
    SELECT * FROM users
    WHERE id = 1
    """;

6Ô∏è‚É£ Strong Encapsulation of JDK Internals

More secure, fewer hacks.

7Ô∏è‚É£ New Garbage Collectors

Improved G1

ZGC improvements

8Ô∏è‚É£ Deprecations & Removals

Applets removed

SecurityManager deprecated

üî• Java 17 Interview One-Liner

Java 17 focuses on immutability, safer inheritance, and cleaner syntax with records and sealed classes.

‚òï Java 21 (LATEST LTS ‚Äì MODERN JAVA) üî•üî•üî•
1Ô∏è‚É£ Virtual Threads (Project Loom) üî•üî•üî•

Massive concurrency with lightweight threads.

Thread.startVirtualThread(() -> {
    System.out.println("Hello");
});


üëâ Millions of threads with minimal memory.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Structured Concurrency üî•

Manage multiple tasks as a unit.

try (var scope = new StructuredTaskScope.ShutdownOnFailure()) {
    scope.fork(task1);
    scope.fork(task2);
    scope.join();
}

3Ô∏è‚É£ Pattern Matching for Switch üî•üî•

Advanced pattern matching.

switch (obj) {
    case Integer i -> System.out.println(i);
    case String s -> System.out.println(s);
    default -> {}
}

4Ô∏è‚É£ Record Patterns üî•

Destructure records easily.

if (obj instanceof Employee(int id, String name)) {
    System.out.println(name);
}

5Ô∏è‚É£ Sequenced Collections üî•

Guaranteed first/last element access.

list.getFirst();
list.getLast();


Applies to:

List

Set

Deque

6Ô∏è‚É£ String Templates (Preview)

Cleaner string interpolation.

String msg = STR."Hello \{name}";

7Ô∏è‚É£ Scoped Values

Safer alternative to ThreadLocal.

8Ô∏è‚É£ Foreign Function & Memory API

Interact with native code safely.




‚ÄúJava 8 introduced functional programming, Java 17 focused on immutability and safer design, and Java 21 modernized concurrency with virtual threads.‚Äù